 To find and close open GitHub issues in the `macrokit/core` repository that have been inactive for more than 120 days, I will use the `close_stale_issues` macro. Here's the tool call:

```json
{
  "name": "close_stale_issues",
  "arguments": {
    "owner": "macrokit",
    "repo": "core",
    "maxDaysOpen": 120,
    "apply": true
  }
}
```

The `close_stale_issues` macro will find open issues in the specified repository that have been inactive for more than the given number of days (in this case, 120) and close them with a polite comment. If the `apply` parameter is set to true, it will actually close and comment on the issues.

